---
const cases = [
  {
    eyebrow: "Your life",
    accent: "text-blue-400",
    phrases: [
      "track my morning runs",
      "log what I'm reading this year",
      "show my weekly habit streak",
      "keep a journal my agent writes to",
    ],
  },
  {
    eyebrow: "Your work",
    accent: "text-violet-400",
    phrases: [
      "show me today's support tickets",
      "deploys by environment this week",
      "pipeline health per service",
      "incidents my on-call agent triaged",
    ],
  },
  {
    eyebrow: "Your agents",
    accent: "text-emerald-400",
    phrases: [
      "what did my research agent find today",
      "log every decision my coding agent made",
      "summarize overnight runs",
      "show tool-call costs for the week",
    ],
  },
  {
    eyebrow: "Your home",
    accent: "text-amber-400",
    phrases: [
      "energy use by hour",
      "indoor air quality today",
      "smart-plug activity log",
      "garden sensor readings",
    ],
  },
];
---

<section id="use-cases" class="relative border-t border-white/5 py-24 sm:py-32">
  <div class="mx-auto max-w-6xl px-6">
    <div class="max-w-2xl">
      <p class="text-sm font-medium text-zinc-500">What you'd ask for</p>
      <h2
        class="mt-2 text-3xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-white sm:text-4xl"
      >
        Whatever you care enough to track.
      </h2>
      <p class="mt-4 text-lg text-zinc-400">
        If you can describe it to Claude, it can become a dashboard. Here are
        a few phrasings that work.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="mt-16 grid gap-6 md:grid-cols-2">
      {
        cases.map((c) => (
          <div class="group relative overflow-hidden rounded-xl border border-white/10 bg-white/[0.02] p-8 transition hover:border-white/20">
            <div class="flex items-center gap-3">
              <span class={`font-mono text-xs uppercase tracking-wider ${c.accent}`}>
                ◆
              </span>
              <span class="text-sm font-medium text-white">{c.eyebrow}</span>
              <span class="h-px flex-1 bg-white/5" />
            </div>
            <ul class="mt-6 space-y-3">
              {c.phrases.map((p) => (
                <li class="flex items-start gap-3 text-sm">
                  <span class="mt-1 font-mono text-[11px] text-zinc-600">
                    &gt;
                  </span>
                  <span class="font-mono text-zinc-300">{p}</span>
                </li>
              ))}
            </ul>
          </div>
        ))
      }
    </div>

    <p class="mt-10 text-center text-sm text-zinc-500">
      Nothing goes to a server somewhere. Every dashboard lives on your
      laptop.
    </p>
  </div>
</section>
